From: =?UTF-8?q?K=C3=A9vin=20Remondi=C3=A8re?= <remondiere@openclaw.local>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 20:08:10 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] feat: MTP speculative decoding support for
 Qwen3.5-35B-A3B MoE

C++ runtime: NEXTN tensors in QWEN35MOE arch, nextn_predict_layers
in hparams, TENSOR_SKIP + nextn loading, MTP forward branch via
build_mtp_tail(), MTP layers marked non-recurrent (attention not GDN).

Python convert: Qwen3_5MoeModel mapping 785 HF mtp.* tensors to
blk.40.* GGUF, MoE expert merging, nextn vocab duplication.

Tested: IQ3_S-MTP (18.38 GB, 755 tensors) loads at 94 tok/s on
RTX 5060 Ti. First MTP GGUF for Qwen3.5 MoE on consumer hardware.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
